sp honey. Allow to reduce for a few minutes, watching carefully to avoid burning, until it becomes a sticky glaze, then set aside.","Add reserved pak choi and broccoli florets into mixing bowl and combine <nobr>10 sec\/\/speed 2<\/nobr>. Transfer into a serving dish. Transfer duck breasts onto a cutting board, slice diagonally and transfer to a serving dish containing vegetables. Drizzle duck with glaze and serve hot with rice."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["15 g fresh ginger, peeled, cut into thin slices (2-3 mm)","2 garlic cloves","½ - 1 fresh red chilli, deseeded if preferred (optional)","700 g duck breast fillets, skin on","1 ½ - 2 tbsp Chinese five spice powder (see Tips), to taste","2 pinches salt, plus extra to taste","1200 g water","2 tsp Vegetable stock paste (refer to the recipe in Basic Cookbook)","80 g soy sauce","200 g long-grain white rice","200 g pak choi, cut into pieces","100 g broccoli florets, cut into pieces (2 cm)","250 g fresh mushrooms","2 tsp toasted sesame oil (10 g)","2 ½ - 3 tbsp honey (approx. 80 g)"]}],"id":"r156331","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-QhnZVgRoEHU\/XZQwBLTUSuI\/AAAAAAAAch4\/24BvX_J9rwM8WfciwurBM6obmb72nULaQCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_R7BL9OuNqVj9Jggb.png","title":"Five-spice duck with mushrooms, Asian vegetables and rice","publishedAt":"2017-05-08T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"42 g","fat":"20 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"60 g","calories":"2512 kJ \/ 600 kcal"},"usefulItems":"kitchen towel, paper towel, frying pan, serving bowl, jug, small bowl, serving dish, fish slice, stove top","hintsAndTricks":["To make homemade five-spice powder place <nobr>2 teaspoons<\/nobr> Sichuan peppercorns, <nobr>3 star<\/nobr> anise, <nobr>2 teaspoons<\/nobr> dried fennel seeds, <nobr>2 cinnamon<\/nobr> sticks and <nobr>6 cloves<\/nobr> into a clean and dry mixing bowl and dry-roast <nobr><strong>5 min\/Varoma\/\/speed 1.<\/strong><\/nobr> Remove mixing bowl lid, set mixing bowl aside and allow  to cool for <n